```
var proto = module.exports = function(options) {
  [...]

  function router(req, res, next) {
    router.handle(req, res, next);
  }

  [...]

  return router;
};
```

A function that returns another function. For me this is too exotic and hard to follow.

And then, instead of adding class instance **methods** using `Router.prototype.xxxx = function() {}` the code defines those methods with `proto.method_name = function() {}`.

Taking a look to the `use()` method defined as `proto.use = function(fn) {}`, it uses `this` internally. In this no-context it is so hard to determine what `this` is.

